Further calls Vegetarierbund to Weltvegantag on 1 November.
The Vegetarierbund Germany proposes on the occasion of the Weltvegantags on 1 November, a series of vegan alternatives:
Pure vegetable margarine is a good alternative to butter, yogurt will be replaced by soy yogurt.
Instead of soy milk, oats, almond or rice milk can be used.
Aufschlagbare plants replace traditional cream whipped cream.
Also there are eggs herbal alternatives.
A half-crushed, ripe banana, for example, can replace an egg as a binder in a cake.
Also Apfelmus 50 grams or a tablespoon of ground flaxseed plus three tablespoons of water are suitable for them.
Doughs are loosely with egg, for example, with a mixture of a teaspoon of baking powder, a tablespoon of starch and three Esslöffeln mineral water.
But even 50 grams of soy yogurt or silk strained tofu can serve this purpose.
According to the Vebu feed currently around 800000 people in Germany are vegan, purely vegetable.
